Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #kettle{}.

Peel the @garlic cloves{2}. Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks.

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with 1/2 tsp @salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes. Add the potatoes and peeled garlic cloves to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml} with the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts). Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{} and set the dressing aside for now.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain and allow to steam uncovered for ~{2%minutes}.

Return to the pan, off the heat. Mash the potatoes with a #potato masher{}, ensuring the mixture isn't too smooth so that some small chunks of potato remain.

Stir in the @chipotle paste{20%g}, Cheddar cheese, @breadcrumbs{50%g} and @salt{} (see pantry for amount). Crumble in half the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g}. Season with pepper and mix together.

Allow the mixture to cool slightly, then shape into 2cm thick patties, 3 per person.

Transfer the potato cakes to a large, lightly oiled #baking tray{}. Drizzle over some @olive oil{} then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{24-26%minutes}. Carefully turn halfway through.

A few minutes before the potato cakes are ready, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat, crumble in the remaining Greek style salad cheese and season with pepper.

Add the @wild rocket{20%g} and @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the dressing bowl and toss together.

Once ready, transfer the cheesy chipotle potato cakes to your plates.

Serve the peas and salad alongside, along with the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} for dipping.

Enjoy!